msgstr "14. Good "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 142. Ācayagāmisutta → ācayagāmīsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an10.142:0.3"
msgid "142. Ācayagāmisutta "
msgstr "142. Accumulation "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.142:1.1"
msgid "“Ācayagāmiñca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi apacayagāmiñca. "
msgstr "“I will teach you the principle that leads to accumulation and that which leads to dispersal. … "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.3"
msgid "katamo ca, bhikkhave, ācayagāmī dhammo? "
msgstr "And what is the principle that leads to accumulation? "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.4"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—"
msgstr "Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom. "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ācayagāmī dhammo. "
msgstr "This is called the principle that leads to accumulation. "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.6"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, apacayagāmī dhammo? "
msgstr "And what is the principle that leads to dispersal? "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.7"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—"
msgstr "Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom. "

msgctxt "an10.142:1.8"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, apacayagāmī dhammo”ti. "
msgstr "This is called the principle that leads to dispersal.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.142:1.9"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

